{
  "stem": "25809.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We got in one evening.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I never saw the outside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I never got out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Only [DRINKS] a few months later, my father had found a place for my, for me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My sister went somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He found a place, which was the chauffeur of an uncle of mine that lived in Utrecht, who had chauffeured for my uncle.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And they were willing to take me in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And my cousin by the name of Andre, that I just mentioned, he was already there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, he was a-- yeah, he was a Rubens.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But because his mother had married, he was a van der Stam.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His name was--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Van der Stam is V-slash-D-- abbreviated-- Stam is S-T-A-M.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then so Andre was, was already there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The people where I went to, I even don't remember how I got there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All I remember at the place, [NON-ENGLISH], we had a lady that had us underground, and food was starting to get scarce.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And every time when there was any food left, the first thing which she would say is, well, let's finish the food because tomorrow there may be a bomb or we may not, we may not ever have a chance to eat it.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she was always eating up whatever that was left on the table.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In those days, all I had was short pants, and it was starting to get chilly.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had continuously cold legs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Cold is one of the underlying factors that seemed to follow me through the entire war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was cold, cold, cold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Anyhow, I went to Utrecht to the, to the ex-chauffeur of my uncle.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The names of the people was-- his name was Kees van Amerongen and Tanta Dien Amerongen, Tanta Dien-- Auntie Dean-- and Uncle Kees.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
